
UC27 Alert Users by Email Use Case

An event requiring an email alert has occurred. 

An email alert is sent out to the iTrust user in the event of a changed password , status change in laboratory procedure , comprehensive report requested and generated. //Note to students: the iTrust system does NOT currently support actual email sending, only a “fake” email sending facility. All email notifications should be executed through the fake email utility.//

    The user has successfully changed his/her password [[requirements:uc3(UC3, S2)]]. An email informing the user of the password change is sent to the user including the MID but not the password.
    The status of a laboratory procedure has been updated [[requirements:uc26(UC26, S3)]]. The patient is notified with the following information: the LOINC number and the updated status.

None


